body:
Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)

```
module m1;
   wire val1 = '0;
endmodule

module m2;
   wire val2 = '1;
endmodule

module s;
   parameter A = 0;
//   generate
      if (A == 1) begin : gen_scope
        m1 m1;
      end
      else if (A == 2) begin : gen_scope
        m2 m2;
      end
//   endgenerate
endmodule

module t;
   s #(0) s0();
   s #(1) s1();
   s #(2) s2();
   initial begin
      if (s1.gen_scope.m1.val1 != '0) $stop;
      if (s2.gen_scope.m2.val2 != '1) $stop;
      $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
      $finish;
   end
endmodule
```

```
%Error: t/t_gen_ifelse.v:32:24: Can't find definition of 'm1' in dotted scope/variable: 's1.gen_scope.m1'
   32 |       if (s1.gen_scope.m1.val1 != '0) $stop;
      |                        ^~
        ... Known scopes under 's1.gen_scope': m2
```

This seems to work with Questa: https://github.com/openhwgroup/cvw/blob/0eed57a0b797273ea38c2f5014e99b60244db775/src/ifu/ifu.sv#L321

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
```

bin/verilator --version
Verilator 5.019 devel rev v5.018-85-gc5ba6e22f
```

What OS and distribution are you using?

```
uname -a
Linux loran 4.18.0-526.el8.x86_64 #1 SMP Sat Nov 18 00:54:11 UTC 2023 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
```

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

